### Step 5: Move all direct Supabase calls into services

**Today — 4 components bypass the service layer:**

| Component | Direct call | Should go to |
|-----------|------------|-------------|
| Profile.jsx line 94 | `supabase.from('profiles').select('id').eq('username',...)` | `authService.checkUsernameAvailable()` (from Step 2) |
| Profile.jsx line 148 | `supabase.storage.from('avatars').upload(...)` | New: `authService.uploadAvatar(userId, blob)` |
| PublicVault.jsx line 63 | `supabase.from('profiles').select('*').eq('username',...)` | Already exists: `authService.getProfileByUsername()` |
| SharedVault.jsx line 63 | `supabase.from('profiles').select('*').eq('username',...)` | Already exists: `authService.getProfileByUsername()` |
| AdminPromptRow.jsx line 16 | `supabase.from('prompts').update({ is_public: !... })` | New: `promptService.togglePublic(id, currentValue)` |

**What to add to services:**

```js
// Add to authService.js
uploadAvatar: async (userId, blob) => {
  const filePath = `${userId}.webp`;
  const { error } = await supabase.storage
    .from('avatars')
    .upload(filePath, blob, { upsert: true, contentType: 'image/webp' });
  if (error) throw error;
  const { data: { publicUrl } } = supabase.storage.from('avatars').getPublicUrl(filePath);
  await authService.updateProfile(userId, { avatar_url: publicUrl });
  return publicUrl;
},

// Add to promptService.js (the Supabase section)
export const togglePromptPublic = async (promptId, currentValue) => {
  const { error } = await supabase
    .from('prompts')
    .update({ is_public: !currentValue })
    .eq('id', promptId);
  if (error) throw error;
};
```

**Then** replace the direct `supabase.from(...)` calls in each component with the service function.

**Effort:** 40 minutes. **Files changed:** 5 (2 services + 3 components).

